title: Ground News - Australian security agencies on increased alert following death of Australians in Lebanon
text:
Summary by Sky News Australia Australian security agencies are on increased alert after two Australians were killed in an Israeli air strike in south Lebanon. Hezbollah has claimed that one of the Australian citizens killed was a fighter for the terrorist group. National security experts warn there is a heightened risk of Australians joining overseas terrorist organisations, particularly those planning attacks against Israel.
